  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Water education and culture, snow and glaciers, and urban environments: implementing the IHP VIII Phase in the Andean subregion</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To deal with contemporaneous socio-environmental changes and challenges, integrated, multidisciplinary and environmentally rigorous approaches to water resources protection and management are essential. IHP-LAC addresses water security in the scope of IHP VIII themes, particularly in the Andean Member States, encompassing education and culture - regional working group, snow and glaciers - regional programme, critical areas on water-related disasters and hydrological changes, groundwater resources, water scarcity and quality, human settlements and ecohydrology. In this subregional context, on-going interdisciplinary processes in the region with a strong Andean component including the Spiritual Reserves of the Humanity and mangroves and sustainable development will be specially supported.</narrative>
  </description>
